TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jones, Charles I.
T1  - The Shape of Production Functions and the Direction of Technical Change*
PY  - 2005
Y1  - 2005/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/120.2.517
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 120
IS  - 2
SP  - 517
EP  - 549
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This pai&gt;er views the standard production function in macroeconomics as a reduced form and derives its properties from microfoundations. The shape of this production function is governed by the distribution of ideas. If that distribution is Pareto, then two results obtain: the global production function is Cobb-Douglas, and technical change in the long run is labor-augmenting. Kortum showed that Pareto distributions are necessary if search-based idea models are to exhibit steady-state growth. Here we show that this same assumption delivers the additional results about the shape of the production function and the direction of technical change.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/120.2.517
ER  - 



